            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-14T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-14T03:00:00-05:00" n="1022" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1022">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.5493/11–1449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-14T16:00:00+08:00">November 14, 1949—4 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 14—12:15 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1992. Re Embtel [<hi rend="italic">my</hi>] 1941, November 8. Letter November 7
                    to Chou En-lai re Military Attaché Soule exit permit was returned by mail today
                    without acknowledgement or comment.</p>
                <p>Re Embtel 396, November 14,<note n="13" xml:id="d1022fn13">Same as telegram No.
                        2413 from Nanking, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> believe in
                    circumstances new note to Chou at this stage would be fruitless. Believe it
                    would be better await further developments Nanking. Effect of any note to
                    Peiping authorities should shortly be discernible Nanking and if communication
                    quite without effect new note would be for present useless. Re Embtel 394,
                    November 14,<note n="12" xml:id="d1022fn12">Not printed.</note> suggest Bacon
                    apply formally direct Labor Bureau as “representative” club if feasible.</p>
                <pb facs="0860" n="850" xml:id="pg_850"/>
                <p>Department’s instructions requested.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 1992. Department pass Nanking 1155.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
